                            <comment id="13023067" author="dvryaboy" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 02:32:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch by Travis Crawford implements the change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that as written, the patch depends on Hadoop&apos;s MAPRECUDE-787 which is available in CDH3 and Hadoop 0.21. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looks like 787 was also rolled into the yahoo distribution, so it may be available in the security branch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13023340" author="traviscrawford" created="Fri, 22 Apr 2011 20:06:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Given how widespread the distributedcache-classpath issue is, its likely this would cause issues at many sites unless its optional for a period of time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would this make sense to make optional via a property, which defaults to the current behavior?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13066250" author="alangates" created="Fri, 15 Jul 2011 23:12:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking this as submitpatch so we can review it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13149222" author="julienledem" created="Sun, 13 Nov 2011 05:42:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2010&quot; title=&quot;Bundle registered jars via distributed cache&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-2010&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-2010&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;_a.patch adds a unit test and adds support for some versions of Hadoop with peculiar distributed cache behavior&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13149224" author="dvryaboy" created="Sun, 13 Nov 2011 05:53:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Re-submitting patch for review.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;FWIW, this patch (applied to 0.8.1) has been running at Twitter in production for a couple of weeks now with no issues, so we are fairly confident in it.  It significantly decreases job creation overhead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13209058" author="dvryaboy" created="Thu, 16 Feb 2012 01:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sooo... I am going to commit this, &apos;k?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
